content.detailedDescription: It was at about 10 pm me and my brother were driving home from work just talking and carrying on, thats when i looked to the sky. i seen a blue orb shoot across the sky. it went what seemed a few hundred feet in a couple seconds the dissipated. then another one shot out from the same spot the last one shot out. again a few hundred feet before dissipating. this happened over and over for about ten minutes.

content.detailedDescription: 2 ball like objects flew over head. they appeared to be flying at a rate of speed similar to a jumbo jet. they were orange in color and flying approximately 1-3 miles apart. there was a large jet that flew ahead of these spheres and one behind. they were alike a bright orange in color. these objects were viewed by myself, my wife, and my three sons.
content.summary: One jet went through. shortly after it was the two objects mentioned above. then a second plane behind. all wee at a  very high rate of speed.

content.detailedDescription: A friend and i were coming back from fishing when we were headed back to the house from the pasture. we noticed a bright light or orb to the right of us we first thought it was a planet but it was moving slowly and made no noise. we decided to go to the house and grab a few binoculars to see if we could get more detail of the object when i looked at it i could see this round object with bright lights on it. i snapped a few photos but it seemed like it was far off we went back in the house for a bit and come back out to see it was gone all the sudden we looked down across the tree line and we saw the same light only this time it was close to the ground stayed there a little bit and then vanished.. it was my first time i have ever seen anything like it..
content.summary: It was a large circle with glowing lights in it

content.detailedDescription: This occurred early in the morning on october7, 2016 over the gulf of mexico, looking southeast from rosemary beach, fl.   this is not the first time that i and my family have seen the objects in question.  this particular time there appeared to be 10 - 15 objects clustered at high altitude above the gulf.  the objects appear to spin and make rapid direction changes while moving at high speed.  they also appear to change color quite rapidly.  these objects are visible for relatively long periods of time...Usually between 30 mins and 1 -2 hours...And always appear in clusters of similar objects.  we live between tyndall and eglin air force bases, so i suppose they could be associated with either one, but if they are then there are some crazy experimental aircraft that the government is keeping under wraps....Attached a video of one of the objects...The video is zoomed pretty significantly, but at the end i zoom back out and you can get a sense of the altitude.
content.summary: More than 10 objects over gulf of mexico...

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking outside at around 11:oo. i could hear a jet aircraft over head so i looked up to see if i could identify it. at first all i cold see was a bright colored dot in the sky moving slowly to the west. i turned out that the dot was a military looking jet aircraft in a near vertical climb. i was able to make it out as a swept wing jet after it leveled out and flew south at a very high rate of speed. that is when i noticed the path that was cut through the clouds above me. it was nearly a cloudless day except for this one wispy bank of clouds overhead. now i'm a retired air force aircraft technician. i've watched aircraft fly through clouds a hundred time and i have never see one cut a visible path through the clouds. another odd thing was the path didn't go from one side of the cloud bank to the other. it started inside the clouds and ended inside the clouds. the attached image shows one end of the objects path, but not shown is the other end which looks very much like the end shown in the image. 
now we have military jets flying around here all the time. normally f-18 colored gray of something dark like gray. this aircraft that was doing the vertical climb was white in color which was odd and i was unable to identify the type of aircraft. all i could see was the swept wings. to be honest it liked a little like and old f-4 phantom but it wasn't. the fact that it was in a vertical climb was odd as well. it was obvious the aircraft was in a hurry to reach the altitude of the disturbance in the clouds. when it reached the disturbance it flew at a very high rate of speed to the south. i was actually surprised to see how fast it was travailing. the aircraft soon returned flying to the north along the disturbance in the clouds.
attached is the path cut in the clouds. the path goes from south to north with the visible end to the south. strange stuff if you ask me.
content.summary: I did not see the object but i see the path and disturbance it left behind in the clouds

content.detailedDescription: I was looking through my 8 inch reflector telescope waiting for venus to show up as the first light/star to the west. when i first saw the object i thought it was venus because it was the first light in the sky. i aligned my telescope on what i thought was venus but low and behold it was a square object (see attached image) floating in the sky with another much smaller square object going around it. i couldn't believe what i was seeing but i was seeing it. i watched the object for several seconds just floating stationary with the smaller object going around it than the object exploded. it was something to see. i didn't see anything hit the object it just exploded. i wasn't like a hollywood movie explosion it was more like what you see in actual war footage. i was able to follow one piece of the object as it fell toward the ground. it was leaving a trail of sparks and what looked like it could have been smoke as it fell. i was able to follow it for a second or two than i lost it. at the time of this sighting i was an aircraft structural mechanic in the us air force. i know what aircraft look like in the sky and this was no aircraft. years later i was able to see what looked like the same object on youtube. it was titled something like a pyramid ufo over a chinese nuclear power plant. i cant vouch for the video but the object shown is very much real. the image i attached is a capture from that video.
content.summary: The ufo was in the shape of a square standing on its edge with another small square going around it in a clockwise direction.

content.summary: Silver/gray disk, resembled an old galvanized garbage can cover.

content.detailedDescription: I took my dog out at 12:26 a.M. on 10/09/2016 and noticed a bright orange light moving toward me from what looked like several miles to the north. even though it wasn't a typical white landing light, at first i thought it was a commercial flight coming into nashville international airport (bna) which is about one mile to my immediate west, on a usual north-south landing pattern.  the orange light, however, did not follow a landing pattern toward the northern end of the bna runways.  instead, it kept on a bit more of a southeasterly bearing coming more or less right over me. i still was not alarmed because sometimes small craft like single or double engine prop planes, or helicopters, will come over me from the north and hook west to make landings at the southern end of the bna runways.  the orange light kept approaching and came in close overhead and a bit toward the west toward bna.  what caught my attention was it had no starboard (green) or port (red) landing lights, no white light, and no blinking lights.  also, it was silent.  at the apparent brightness and speed it was traveling (like a fast moving helicopter) i should have been able to hear engine noise, but it was dead silent.  then, it disappeared.  it was like it  switched off its bright orange light. it took a couple of seconds for it to go completely out, like the filament in the bulb was still hot, but then it went dead out.  i thought, "man, i wish my wife merri had been out here with me to see that!"  i let my dog back in but i stayed outside for a few minutes watching to the north.  son of a gun, just about five minutes later, another orange light appeared in the north.  this time, i ran in and woke up merri.  she came out and we watched as the second orange light did the same thing as the first one, but this time, the light went out much sooner as it approached us heading south.  merri went back in and said "holler if you see more."  about five minutes later, here came another one out of the north!  i got binoculars and zoomed in on this one. it seemed to be a single, bright orange light with no green or red or white lights, and no blinking lights, and no discernible shape or fuselage. this one went all the way over us, stayed on a bit longer, then finally quickly faded out.  merri stayed outside with me this time. about five minutes later, here came three orange lights in from the north.  they seemed to be in single file, much like you see when commercial flights approach from the north.  but the one out front suddenly went out, leaving two.  one of them hooked to the west far short of the northern end of bna's runways, then it went out.  the remaining one seemed to continue its approach toward us like the single ones had done, but it went out much earlier than the first ones we saw. between 12:26 a.M. and about 1:40 a.M. there were about 14 flying orange lights observed - 6 singles, two triples, and one double. no red, green or white lights were ever spotted. only the single ones came close to us and right overhead. no blinking lights were observed even when they were pretty much straight overhead.  no noise was heard.  all of them seemed to turn off their orange light and vanish.  in a lifetime of stargazing and sky watching i have never seen anything like this.  especially the repeat performances.  what were they?  maybe drones?  maybe the same three or so objects circling around bna?  maybe 14 or more separate objects?  i hope there's a logical explanation, but i don't believe licensed aircraft are allowed to just turn off their lights and vanish like that.  anybody have any ideas?  oh yeah, p.S. i stayed outside awhile longer.  i didn't see any more moving orange lights. it was about 2:11 a.M. when i heard a helicopter approaching from the east heading over me and moving toward bna.  i looked at it through binoculars. it had a red port light, a green starboard light, and a blinking white light.  i could see some of it's structure.  it was moving at about the same apparent speed as the orange lights but it was loud! i had no doubt it was a chopper and i thought it might have been a military flight out of smyrna air base 10 or 12 miles to my southeast. maybe it kept more orange lights away???!!!???
content.summary: Soldi, bright, orange lights, no green red or white lights, no strobe

content.detailedDescription: I woke up at 1am went to kitchen sink to get a drink of water and looked out the window, there were 2 horizontal rows of bright red lights about the size of large plate,maybe 12-14 in each row, there were also a white/green light on the top. i could not see the shape of the object because it was very dark out in the field behind our house. my husband had gotten up and i called him into the kitchen and pointed out the window, that's when we noticed round lights above the  tree line about a quarter of a mile north of us, my husband went to the back door for a better look and counted 19 of them stretched out over half a mile, the object in the field was totally silent.For a reason i still don't understand we just went back to bed, i didn't even lay awake thinking about what i had just seen i went right to sleep. wish i had gotten some pictures
content.summary: Woke up at 1am got a drink at the kitchen sink and saw objects out window husband saw it too.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking to get in my vehicle at 4:11 am on 10/9/16. the sky was very clear. i looked up at the constellation orion. i hesitated a moment because it was so bright. then three white orbs in a triangle configuration flew overhead. they came from the southeast to northwest in downtown northville mi it only took about 2 seconds to fly from horizon to horizon and out of sight......No noise. i felt very lucky to see it. wow!

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were at a friends fish fry for the evening. we were sitting around a campfire. it was kind of cold out. i got up and went inside to the bathroom. when i returned to the fire i turned around to warm my backside. that's when i saw what i first thought was the pleiades in the sky. but as soon as my eyes focused i saw that it was lights in a triangle shape and i said, what's that! pointing to the object. everybody started to get up and look.(there were 6 of us). 5 of us saw it. it was traveling fast away and went over a tree in the distance and was gone. we stood there for the rest of the evening talking about it and wondering if anyone else saw it. somebody had to of seen it besides us.
content.summary: Triangled shaped lights traveling faster than normal with no sound

content.detailedDescription: I was laying on my couch, trying to sleep but couldn't. i was looking out my balcony window into the sky. i live near the beach in a high rise building so i often look outside at the night sky, never see anything out of the ordinary. i was trying to sleep, so i look outside and see about 5 or 6 red lights in a straight line (west to east). at first in was farther away north of me up the coast. i wrote it off thought nothing of it. i looked again a minute later and saw the same red lights, but closer to me, still at a distance. thought it odd, but still didn't thing much of it. i looked again, saw the same lights, but even closer and more pronounced. i could now see a matted silver or grey outline of a saucer shaped craft. when i saw this, i shot up, sat upright on my couch. gazing harder and felt scared because it seemed like the craft was focusing directly on me. when i sat up and stared at the red lights and shape of he craft, i felt that it stared back at me, then darted away(smoothly)at a ne angle and disappeared. i had nothing to reference the size or distance, but knew it got closer to me and clearer each time i looked at it. the scariest part for me was the feeling that it was focusing on me, because as soon as i sat up and looked at it, it flew away. i ran back to my bed freaked out, feel like i will never sleep again at this point.
content.summary: Looked out balcony and saw 5 or 6 red lights hovering. seemed to mover closer to me. i sat up and stared, saw silver or grey saucer shape. when i sat up, it immediately move down east into sky and disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: Observed large craft with solid red light in the center and a large bright white strobe on either side. hovered south of rincon mountains for approximately 15 minutes. observed craft through binoculars. object appeared to be at approximately 20,000 ft. strobes stopped flashing and the object began moving nw as a solid red orb. object passed overhead and no sound was observed. the red orb gained altitude and speed at an unusually high rate until it had disappeared from view to the nw. there were slight abrupt directional changes to the north and south as it moved away. no other air traffic was observed during the entire duration of the sighting, which is unusual for the area.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Solid red light with an extremely bright white strobe on either side. hovered for 15 minutes. strobes stoped and the craft accelerated to unusually high speed.

content.detailedDescription:
My husband and i were settling into the hot tub about 8:30pm, friday, october 7, 2016. as i was reclining with my head to the west, i saw a blur in my peripheral vision to the left or northeast. i sat up to see it better since there were supposed to be good meteor sightings that night. i caught it full view as it was heading west but was banking sharply such that the right edge was at the bottom. i could clearly see pale rose colored lights along the boomerang shaped edges only. the nose was curved and not pointed. the lights were not brilliant but subdued and did not waiver or flicker but rather stayed constant. the lights ran along the edge of the boomerang pointing down. from the edge of the lights the back spread out to make what appwarred to be a solid area. there was a back edge that was slightly curved outward from the back keeping it from being a triangle shape. this back area seemed slightly reflective making it look solid but not sharply visible and as if it were reflecting the stars and lights above it. it was moving maybe 200 feet above the tops of the houses. i knew it was some sort of craft but was not sure what it was. 

it levelled out as the front tip was orienting to the north so that the lights were pointed directly toward the ground and it continued moving north until i could no longer see it. 

there was absolutely no sound and no bright lights. it was a mere few seconds and we saw and heard planes at varying heights after the event. we had seen and heard plamesprior to. we even saw a few meteors after the event. we stayed out in the hot tub for nearly 90 minutes and never witnessed anything else unusual. i was a little freaked out because it was unlike anything i had ever seen and we have been star gazing for over a year in our hot tub at varying times of the evening and night. i was not afraid but very very curious.
 i have a very rough sketch in pencil and am working on a better sketch with colorthat i can send in a day or so.
content.summary: Craft moved over neighbor houses from east, banked and went north then kept going until disappeared from view.

content.detailedDescription: I was about to leave to go to the store with my wife and boys at 8pm sharp when i came out of the apartment a very bright light caught my attention in the distance it seem to be alot brighter and lower than any other star so immediately i started walking closer to get a better view and started taking video i zoomed in as close as possible there were several children and teenagers outside and they all gathered and took out their phones to get video. one of the kids had a better phone that zoomed in closer and he caught the fleet of ufos blinking surrounding the bigger one that my phone captured video of. the object was stationary for quite sum time and seemed to decende slowly eventually behind the trees out of our focus. i knew it wasnt any aircraft or helicopter which we usally see in our part of the neighborhood and usually they move and use spotlights. these objects seem to be attracted to the big moving lights in the sky at the universal studios because they all were hovering parallel to the big universal lights. there were planes passing by in the area one past slightly under the object.We were all in agreement that these objects were not aircrafts or stars.
content.summary: Ufo was seen hovering an blinking in colorful display also have more video with better camara with better zoom showin multiple objects blinking around main object in fleet formation.

content.detailedDescription: My husband was working outdoors when he noticed long webs falling from the sky.  he looked up and saw innumerable webs falling, he called me out and we noticed a glowing ball making a large grid pattern, high in the sky.  it was ejecting a trail, as wide as the ball of light, of super sticky web-like material that seemed to reflect the light. it was silent.  we watched the orb, high in the sky, for about 15 minutes and don't know how long it was up there as we had to get back to work. he first noticed it at around 11:30 am and we just got a huge sample from out of the sky at 5:45 pm - it is still falling. there is no sign of the orb now.  our whole property and our neighbors property totaling at least 53 acres had quite a bit of it draped around.  we went to a yard sale at 3:30pm about 6 miles away and it was draped around their yard also.  when it first fell it seemed like it dissolved on touch and was hard to collect.  later it got more solid and real sticky. the substance was hard to avoid and it clung like crazy to my husband and myself as well as the house, cars, fence, trees, etc. it was hard to get off, even with water. i am very worried if this substance will make us ill.  i am wondering if anybody else reported this.
content.summary: Glowing orb flying in grid with trail of web/lights coming out-we have web sample

content.detailedDescription:
I was laying on my bed next to a window just looking straight up not looking for anything and an orb or round shape traveled across my field of vision at approximately 30 miles an hour or faster, traveling from south to north. it was burnt orange and emitting a burnt orange light or energy. the sun was south and in no way was shining through it. it was not transparent. it was not a balloon. it traveled at a constant speed in one direction.

i have read many ufo reports but didn't really believe them until i saw it with my own eyes. i had to see it to believe it. this has changed the way i understand this reality. i didn't even think of getting a picture until after the event.
content.summary: Looking straight up outside window, burnt orange 3ft to 20ft traveling in one direction within field of view

content.detailedDescription:
my boyfriend and i were sitting on a rooftop. i noticed what looked like a star zipping across the sky, stopping and going, and making strange patterns.  i pointed it out and asked " what could possibly move that fast so high in the sky?"  there was another one even farther away making  similar patterns.   he stared at the flickering star like balls of light for a about a  minute and then it looked like he was getting a little farther away so i took out my phone and recorded it. when i zoomed in  it looked more like a multicolor holographic orb.  my boyfriend said, "i think we're looking at a ufo ."   i had never seen anything like it.  we looked online to see if any local stargazers saw it but nothing came up. it was not until i showed the footage to a friends dad who is a ufo enthusiast and told me to send this in that i heard about mufon. i only wish i got better video. 
'

content.detailedDescription: I was driving my truck on a sunny, clear day at around 3 pm, cloudless sky, and i noticed a "metallic"/shiny long shape in the sky. i first thought it may have been a kite (little or no movement), but after staring more intently, it was obvious it was no kite: much larger, much higher, very long and metallic: it reflected the sun brightly. i stared as intensely as i could while driving (probably inappropriate given the fact i was driving), trying to discern what the object could be: there was no vapor trail, it appeared motionless, oddly shaped (for any aircraft i am familiar with)...I briefly (a second or two?) looked at the road as i was driving and then looked upward: the object was gone! again, totally clear sky...I'm not a "ufologist", a rational, "professional" individual, and i have no rational explanation for what i witnessed..
content.summary: Long, metallic, shiny/reflected sun, like a long "tube"..

content.detailedDescription:
On friday october 7th at 11:45pm while taking out my dog i caught the glimpse of a bright red or reddish orange lighted object hovering at tree top level. 

at first i thought it was a helicopter since we live along the coast and it's not unusual to have coast guard helicopters in the area at night. when i realized the craft was not making noise and not moving from its location i moved my location to get a better viewing. 

the object was at treetop level spinning or looked to be spinning with unusually bright red orange lights. judging by the distance and by trees in the area i would state that the object was roughly 15 feet in height and about a third as wide. 

hoping to catch a photo i ran back to retrieve my phone but when i returned i couldn't llocate the object to take a photo or video.
content.summary: Observed diamond shaped red lighted object
